      </p>

      <h3>Pre-Order Wisely</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Wait for Reviews:</strong> Skip pre-orders unless you're 100% sure</li>
        <li><strong>Digital vs. Physical:</strong> Physical often has better deals</li>
        <li><strong>Pre-Order Bonuses:</strong> Usually cosmetic, rarely worth it</li>
        <li><strong>Pre-Load Benefits:</strong> Play at midnight on release day</li>
        <li><strong>Cancel Anytime:</strong> Most stores allow pre-order cancellation</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Day-One Strategy</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Check reviews before purchasing</li>
        <li>Wait for day-one patches (common for AAA games)</li>
        <li>Look for launch week discounts (10-30% off)</li>
        <li>Consider waiting for Game Pass additions</li>
        <li>Join communities for early impressions</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Avoid Launch Issues</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Download games overnight to avoid server congestion</li>
        <li>Clear storage space before large downloads</li>
        <li>Update system software in advance</li>
        <li>Check minimum PC requirements carefully</li>
        <li>Read recent Steam reviews for technical issues</li>
